Not revoked until after voting
It is not yet clear whether the dismissals of Icelandair’s flight attendants, which are due to take effect at the end of next month, will be revoked.
The electronic voting on the collective bargaining agreement of the Icelandic Aircrew Association on behalf of Icelandair’s aircrew will end tomorrow at noon.
Icelandair’s chairman, Guðlaug Líney Jóhannsdóttir, says she is confident that Icelandair will not make a decision on the layoffs until the outcome of the vote is known.
“There’s definitely a connection,” says Guðlaug Líney.
