And of course, people are eager to know if they will have a job after the end of the month.”
The agreement to be voted on was signed a week ago, on the night of 19 July.
It is expected to be valid until the end of September 2025 and is based on an agreement that was previously voted down by the flight attendants.
On 17 July, the Board of Directors and the Board of Trustees of Icelandair agreed to announce a general strike at Icelandair.
It never took place, but this was decided in the wake of Icelandair’s decision to end negotiations with Flugfreyjufélagið, dismiss all its flight attendants and seek agreements with another trade union.
In addition, the company's pilots were to temporarily take over the duties of security officers on board.
